profile_description:Colombia Cauca Microbial Washed\vAltitude: 1895-1950m | Moisture: 11.2%\vDensity: 796g/L (mid-low) | Aged: 3+ months\vLoad: 120g\v\vVersion 1 - Based on Kaffelogic official\vF-WSH 1500-2200 (SeanBrews v2.2) template.\v\vAdjustments from official template:\v- Preheat 840->820W (matches RWA V1 success,\v  bean is moderately aged but not severely)\v- expect_fc 206->200C (mid-low density 796 g/L\v  predicts actual FC ~192-196C, 6C safety buffer\v  to avoid PID stalling like COL Chiloso V3)\v- expect_colrchange 0->168C (washed bean,\v  slightly higher than natural ~165C)\v- Kd 3.55->3.10 (proven zero negative ROR\v  from RWA V1 + Catimor V3-V5)\v- min_ROR 2.0->0.2 (safer floor, matches RWA V1)\v- Cooldown 16500/15500/100C -> 17000/16000/85C\v  (light roast fast lock for fresh aroma)\v- Roast levels 208-220C -> 203-215C\v  (-5C shift for light roast target)\v\vRoast profile and fan profile kept from official\vF-WSH 1500-2200 template (5-point curve).\vNo Zone, no Corner. Schema 1.4.\v\vExpected FC: ~192-196C\v(template expect_fc=206 lowered to 200 for buffer)\v\vRecommended Levels:\v\v(!) Level 1.0 (203C): NOT recommended -\v   under-development risk for microbial washed\v\vLight: Level 1.5 (~205C, ~14% dev)\v   bright floral/fruit acidity\v\vLight Balanced: Level 2.0 (~207C, ~16-18% dev)\v   *** RECOMMENDED ***\v\vMedium Light: Level 2.5 (~209C, ~18-20% dev)\v   if Light tastes grassy/maltyl/papery\v   (under-developed signal)\v\vMedium: Level 3.0 (~211C, ~20-22% dev)\v   if microbial fermentation needs more\v   Maillard development\v\vMicrobial washed note: yeast/bacteria-fermented\vbeans have higher sugar than traditional washed.\vNeeds sufficient Maillard time to express\vcomplex acidity + fermentation notes.\vAvoid going lighter than Level 1.5.\v\vUnder-roast safeguards (per user request):\v- official template curve (no custom bezier)\v- end_ratio 0.75 kept\v- preheat >=815W kept\v- expect_fc with 4-8C safety buffer\v- recommended_level not below 2.0\v\vC40 pour-over grind: 22-26 clicks\vResting period: 7-14 days\v
